# Power of Two

Formula:

```java
(n > 0) && ((n & (n - 1)) == 0)
```

Examples:

```text
1  -> True
2  -> True
4  -> True
8  -> True
16 -> True

3  -> False
5  -> False
10 -> False
```

---

# Brian Kernighan Algorithm

Count set bits efficiently.

```java
int count = 0;

while(n != 0)
{
    n = n & (n - 1);
    count++;
}
```

Time Complexity:

```text
O(Number of Set Bits)
```

Better than checking all 32 bits.

