# Ultimate Memory Trick

```text
AND (&)  -> CHECK

OR (|)   -> SET

XOR (^)  -> TOGGLE

SHIFT    -> MOVE

n&(n-1)  -> REMOVE RIGHTMOST SET BIT

1<<k     -> CREATE MASK
```

If you memorize only these six lines, you can solve most beginner-to-intermediate bit manipulation questions in Java.
